<refentry xml:id="vtiful-kernel-excel.getConditionalFormats" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
 <refnamediv>
  <refname>Vtiful\Kernel\Excel::getConditionalFormats</refname>
  <refpurpose>Vtiful\Kernel\Excel getConditionalFormats</refpurpose>
 </refnamediv>
 <refsect1 role="description">
  &reftitle.description;
  <methodsynopsis>
   <modifier>public</modifier> <type>array</type><methodname>Vtiful\Kernel\Excel::getConditionalFormats</methodname>
   <void/>
  </methodsynopsis>
  <simpara>Returns the conditional formatting blocks defined on the worksheet currently open for reading.</simpara>
 </refsect1>
 <refsect1 role="parameters">
  &reftitle.parameters;
  &no.function.parameters;
 </refsect1>
 <refsect1 role="returnvalues">
  &reftitle.returnvalues;
  <simpara>An array of conditional formatting blocks, each an associative array with a <literal>range</literal> and a <literal>rules</literal> list. Each rule holds the keys <literal>type</literal>, <literal>operator</literal>, <literal>priority</literal>, <literal>stop_if_true</literal>, <literal>dxf_id</literal>, <literal>percent</literal>, <literal>bottom</literal>, <literal>rank</literal>, <literal>text</literal>, <literal>time_period</literal>, <literal>formula1</literal> and <literal>formula2</literal>. Returns &null; when no worksheet is open for reading.</simpara>
 </refsect1>
</refentry>
